text.tspan: Daily confirmed COVID-19 deaths per million: which countries are bending
Shown is the 7-day rolling average of daily confirmed COVID-19 deaths per million people.
Limited testing and challenges in the attribution of the cause of death means that the number of confirmed deaths may not be
an accurate count of the true number of deaths from COVID-19.
Days since daily confirmed deaths reached 0.1 per million people
